## Project Description
This project is a simple Movie Database application that allows users to add, edit, and delete movies. 
The application fetches movie data from a local server and displays it in the web interface.
Users can add new movies by providing the title, year, and description, and they can also edit or delete existing movies.
 
 ## How To Use
Application Features

   1. Add Movie:
        Enter the movie title, year, and description in the respective input fields.
        Click the "Add Movie" button to add the movie to the database. The movie will appear in the list below the input fields.

   2. Edit Movie:
        Feature not implemented yet.

   3.Delete Movie:
        Each movie entry has a "Delete" button. Clicking this button will remove the movie from the database.

## Setup and Installation
    1. Clone the repository to your local machine.
    2. Navigate to the project directory using the terminal.
    3. Install dependencies using npm install.
    4. Start the local server by running node server.js.
    5. Open index.html in your web browser to access the Movie Database application.

